label: Insignium Romæ templorum prospectus exteriores interioresque: a celebrioribus architectis inventi: nunc tandem suis cum plantis ac mensuris.
description: The online edition of this book in the public domain, i.e., not protected by copyright, has been produced by Emory University Libraries. Manuscript, Archives, and Rare Book Library copy inscribed in ink on front free endpaper: Gmo. Trecourt, 1874. Illustrated copperplate title page. Title page numbered as the first plate. Plates are numbered, but pages are unsigned. Engravers include: Giovanni Francesco Venturini, Jean Collin, Nicholas Vincenzo Mariotti, Valérien Regnart, and Dominique Barriére. A series of 70 copperplate engravings of Roman Renaissance and Baroque churches with floor plans, cross-sections and elevations. Edition: [second edition]. Binding: Vellum binding with blind tooled border on front and back boards. Author, shortened title and year hand lettered on spine. Blue and white endbands. Marbled paste downs (not contemporary).
